BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: COLLEGE STATION ISD COUNCIL OF PARENT

IRS990.Desc: TO ENHANCE THE EDUCATION OF THE STUDENTS ATTENDING COLLEGE STATION ISD SCHOOLS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH CAMPUS SELECTS THEIR OWN OFFICERS DURING THE LATE SPRING. A LETTER IS SENT HOME TO ALL STUDENTS GIVING PARENTS THE OPPORTUNITY TO JOIN AND INQUIRE ABOUT BECOMING AN OFFICER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 8b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THERE ARE NO COMMITTEES WITH AUTHORITY TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE GOVERNING BODY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING BOARD MEETS TO REVIEW A DRAFT TAX RETURN FOR APPROVAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS FOR EACH CAMPUS' PTO ARE NOT READILY AVAILABLE BUT ANYONE CAN REQUEST THE DOCUMENTS THROUGH THE OPEN RECORDS ACT.
